HEADWORD: Suberite
<hw>Su"ber*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>suber</ets> the cork tree.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any
sponge of the genus <gen>Suberites</gen> and allied genera. These
sponges have a fine and compact texture, and contain minute siliceous
spicules.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

